Package org.ejbca.core.model.ra

Class UserDataVO

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ejbca.core.model.ra.UserDataVO
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class UserDataVO
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Deprecated.
    Use org.cesecore.certificates.endentity.EndEntityInformation instead. Since EJBCA 5.0.0.
    Holds admin data collected from UserData in the database. Strings are stored in Base64 encoded format to be safe for storing in database, xml etc. NOTE! This class is not to be extended anymore. It is kept for backwards serialization compatibility only. use class EndEntityInformation instead.
    Version:
    $Id: UserDataVO.java 34165 2020-01-02 15:18:44Z samuellb $
    See Also:

        public String getDN()
        Deprecated.
        User DN as stored in the database. If the registered DN has unused DN fields the empty ones are kept, i.e. CN=Tomas,OU=,OU=PrimeKey,C=SE. See ECA-1841 for an explanation of this. Use method getCertificateDN() to get the DN stripped from empty fields.
        Returns:
        String with DN, might contain empty fields, use getCertificateDN to get without empty fields
        See Also:
        getCertificateDN()

      • getCertificateDN

        public String getCertificateDN()
        Deprecated.
        Returns the DN to be used when creating a certificate (without empty fields). If the registered DN has unused DN fields the empty ones are kept, i.e. CN=Tomas,OU=,OU=PrimeKey,C=SE. See ECA-1841 for an explanation of this. Use method getCertificateDN() to get the DN stripped from empty fields, getDN() returns DN with empty fields.
        Returns:
        String with DN, with no empty fields, use getDN to get including empty fields
        See Also:
        getDN()
